    markdown:
      "## add\n\n`client.v1.contracts.rateCards.rates.add(entitled: boolean, product_id: string, rate_card_id: string, rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM', starting_at: string, billing_frequency?: 'MONTHLY' | 'QUARTERLY' | 'ANNUAL' | 'WEEKLY', commit_rate?: { rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM'; price?: number; tiers?: tier[]; }, credit_type_id?: string, custom_rate?: object, ending_before?: string, is_prorated?: boolean, price?: number, pricing_group_values?: object, quantity?: number, tiers?: { price: number; size?: number; }[]): { data: object; }`\n\n**post** `/v1/contract-pricing/rate-cards/addRate`\n\nAdd a new rate\n\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `entitled: boolean`\n\n- `product_id: string`\n  ID of the product to add a rate for\n\n- `rate_card_id: string`\n  ID of the rate card to update\n\n- `rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM'`\n\n- `starting_at: string`\n  inclusive effective date\n\n- `billing_frequency?: 'MONTHLY' | 'QUARTERLY' | 'ANNUAL' | 'WEEKLY'`\n  Optional. Frequency to bill subscriptions with. Required for subscription type products with Flat rate.\n\n- `commit_rate?: { rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM'; price?: number; tiers?: { price: number; size?: number; }[]; }`\n  A distinct rate on the rate card. You can choose to use this rate rather than list rate when consuming a credit or commit.\n  - `rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM'`\n  - `price?: number`\n    Commit rate price. For FLAT rate_type, this must be >=0. For PERCENTAGE rate_type, this is a decimal fraction, e.g. use 0.1 for 10%; this must be >=0 and <=1.\n  - `tiers?: { price: number; size?: number; }[]`\n    Only set for TIERED rate_type.\n\n- `credit_type_id?: string`\n  The Metronome ID of the credit type to associate with price, defaults to USD (cents) if not passed. Used by all rate_types except type PERCENTAGE. PERCENTAGE rates use the credit type of associated rates.\n\n- `custom_rate?: object`\n  Only set for CUSTOM rate_type. This field is interpreted by custom rate processors.\n\n- `ending_before?: string`\n  exclusive end date\n\n- `is_prorated?: boolean`\n  Default proration configuration. Only valid for SUBSCRIPTION rate_type. Must be set to true.\n\n- `price?: number`\n  Default price. For FLAT and SUBSCRIPTION rate_type, this must be >=0. For PERCENTAGE rate_type, this is a decimal fraction, e.g. use 0.1 for 10%; this must be >=0 and <=1.\n\n- `pricing_group_values?: object`\n  Optional. List of pricing group key value pairs which will be used to calculate the price.\n\n- `quantity?: number`\n  Default quantity. For SUBSCRIPTION rate_type, this must be >=0.\n\n- `tiers?: { price: number; size?: number; }[]`\n  Only set for TIERED rate_type.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ data: { rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'CUSTOM' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE'; commit_rate?: object; credit_type?: object; custom_rate?: object; is_prorated?: boolean; price?: number; pricing_group_values?: object; quantity?: number; tiers?: object[]; }; }`\n\n  - `data: { rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'CUSTOM' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE'; commit_rate?: { rate_type: 'FLAT' | 'PERCENTAGE' | 'SUBSCRIPTION' | 'TIERED' | 'TIERED_PERCENTAGE' | 'CUSTOM'; price?: number; tiers?: object[]; }; credit_type?: { id: string; name: string; }; custom_rate?: object; is_prorated?: boolean; price?: number; pricing_group_values?: object; quantity?: number; tiers?: { price: number; size?: number; }[]; }`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport Metronome from '@metronome/sdk';\n\nconst client = new Metronome();\n\nconst response = await client.v1.contracts.rateCards.rates.add({\n  entitled: true,\n  product_id: '13117714-3f05-48e5-a6e9-a66093f13b4d',\n  rate_card_id: 'd7abd0cd-4ae9-4db7-8676-e986a4ebd8dc',\n  rate_type: 'FLAT',\n  starting_at: '2020-01-01T00:00:00.000Z',\n});\n\nconsole.log(response);\n```",
